      "content": "Stop your running immediately, because shakiness and sweating after exercise are often signs of *low* blood sugar, not high. Do not add insulin right now, as that will only send you into a dangerous hypoglycemic episode. Instead, consume 15 grams of fast-acting carbohydrates, like a few glucose tablets or half a glass of juice, and check your blood sugar in 15 minutes. If you still feel shaky, repeat the carb intake.",
